name "fig:SD"

\end_inset

Imagen taken from 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "HARDI"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This SD technique is ill-posed and affected by noise.
 Later in 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "CSD"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 was introduced a modification to SD called 
\series bold
C
\series default
onstrained 
\series bold
S
\series default
pherical 
\series bold
D
\series default
econvolution (CSD) that preserves the angular resolution while remaining
 robust to noise effects.
 In CSD a non-negativity constraint on the estimated fODF is included into
 the formulation, as negative fibre orientation densities are physically
 impossible.
 Besides, this constraint eliminates the need for low-pass filtering the
 obtained fODF.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Add SH representation
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In order to perform the deconvolution over the sphere, the spherical representat
ion 
\begin_inset Formula $S\left(\theta,\phi\right)$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 can be written as
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
S\left(\theta,\phi\right)=F\left(\theta,\phi\right)\varotimes R\left(\theta\right)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Diffusion Bases Functions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Multi-Tensor Methods
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Multi-tensor representation is a natural extension of the the Diffusion
 Tensor Imaging (DTI) 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "DTI"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 where orientated diffusion along the fascicles is represented with a mixture
 of Gaussian distributions such that
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
E_{i}\left(v\right)=\sum_{k=1}^{M}\alpha_{k}exp\left(-b\mathbf{g}_{i}^{T}D_{k}\left(v\right)\mathbf{g}_{i}\right)\label{eq:multi-tensor-representation}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

